    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive core is headlined by **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Brice Turang** (75.06), both of whom capitalize on prime hitting conditions. **Mickey Moniak** thrives today against Spencer Strider, aided by a +14% park factor and a favorable platoon matchup that overrides the strength of the opposing arm. Similarly, **Brice Turang** earns a strong start by pairing a solid matchup against Zack Littell with his elite ability to contribute to our scarcity-driven SB target. **Seiya Suzuki** (75.03) rounds out our top trio, benefiting from a +10% wind-out advantage that boosts his power potential against Merrill Kelly. We are also looking for **Austin Riley** to exploit the friendly confines of his home park, which accounts for a massive +14% boost to his efficiency score.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Gabriel Moreno** (54.36) out of the catcher rotation. While **Gabriel Moreno** posted a respectable score against Matthew Boyd, he was ultimately edged out by **Dalton Rushing** and **Luis Campusano**. **Dalton Rushing** maintains a higher upside due to favorable SP xERA dynamics and a wind-assisted environment, forcing **Gabriel Moreno** into a reserve role as we maximize our daily game caps. While **Josh Naylor** and **Jose Caballero** round out the bottom of our active lineup, their contributions remain essential to our depth, though **Jose Caballero** faces a steep -13% platoon penalty that requires close monitoring if the game stays tight.\n\nRisks today center primarily on the \"Lineup Pending\" status across our roster, which introduces potential variance if managers shuffle the bottom-third of their orders. We are particularly wary of **Corbin Carroll** (63.44), whose projection is weighed down by a tough matchup against Matthew Boyd and a -8% penalty from the SP's ability to limit SBs; if **Corbin Carroll** is bumped from the three-hole or conditions shift, his floor could drop significantly. We are keeping **Giancarlo Stanton**, **Max Muncy**, **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Cole Young** on high alert, ready to rotate in should any late-inning scratches arise.",
